summary: This clip features an urban street environment captured along Hamilton Avenue. The spectral content is dominated by steady low-frequency hum (0–533 Hz) likely from vehicular engines and ambient urban noise. There are also transient peaks in the mid (2000–4000 Hz) and high (4000–8000 Hz) frequency ranges, suggesting the presence of passing vehicles, occasional sirens, and other street sounds such as potential human activities or mechanical events.
